    <detaileddescription>
<para>Each result element in <ref refid="classnanoflann_1_1RadiusResultSet" kindref="compound">RadiusResultSet</ref>. Note that distances and indices are named <computeroutput>first</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>second</computeroutput> to keep backward-compatibility with the <computeroutput>std::pair&lt;&gt;</computeroutput> type used in the past. In contrast, this structure is ensured to be <computeroutput>std::is_standard_layout</computeroutput> so it can be used in wrappers to other languages. See: <ulink url="https://github.com/jlblancoc/nanoflann/issues/166">https://github.com/jlblancoc/nanoflann/issues/166</ulink> </para>
